      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 128: 🟡 Suggestions - `bodyOverwrite` from plugin data is trusted and rendered as the message body with no validation or size guard. A plugin can now replace arbitrary message text shown in the UI, so malformed or very large values can create spoofing/confusion or UI performance issues. Please constrain this to the intended plugin contract and reject/ignore oversized values before assigning it. For example:\n```suggestion\n    if (auto bodyOverwriteIt \u003d msg.pluginData.find(\"bodyOverwrite\");\n        bodyOverwriteIt !\u003d msg.pluginData.end() \u0026\u0026 !bodyOverwriteIt.value().isEmpty()\n        \u0026\u0026 bodyOverwriteIt.value().size() \u003c\u003d MAX_MESSAGE_BODY_SIZE) {\n        body \u003d bodyOverwriteIt.value();\n    }\n```",
      "revId": "b713d737f1636cf95e1818fdb83e83ddacd6910e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
