      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 137: 🔴 Critical Issues - Edition entries are read from `msg.editions`, but the wrapper only adds `message.pluginData` at the top level. Unless every edition map is explicitly populated with `bodyOverwrite`, edit history will display a mix of overwritten current body and original previous bodies, which can expose untranslated/original plugin-handled content and make editing history inconsistent. Please either define and marshal per-edition plugin data, or leave edition bodies original and name the role/display behavior explicitly. If the intent is per-edition overwrite, ensure the daemon payload contains it and add a regression test covering an edited message with plugin overwrite.",
      "revId": "b713d737f1636cf95e1818fdb83e83ddacd6910e",
